          <div class="article-p">
              <h2>display: flex</h2>
              <p>In order to see the effect of flexible blocks, we need the following construction.</p>

<!-- ****************************************** -->    
<pre><code>
<span class="lang">html</span>
  &lt;div class="d-flex"&gt;
    &lt;div class="item"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="item"&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="item"&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="item"&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

<span class="lang">CSS</span>            
.d-flex{
  display: flex;
  width: 100%;
  min-height: 200px;
}
.item{
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  border: 1px solid #000;
}</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->

              <div class="d-flex">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <P>Excellent. Our blocks are lined up in a horizontal line.</P>

              <h2>justify-content: flex-start (Default value)</h2>
              <p>With this property, we can achieve the initial position of the blocks. This value is set by the browser by default.</p>
<!-- **************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: flex-start;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __start">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>justify-content: center</h2>
              <p>With this property, we can achieve alignment in the center of the horizontal axis.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: center;
}</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
                <div class="d-flex __centr">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              
              <h2>justify-content: flex-end</h2>
              <p>By this property we can achieve that our blocks will be at the end of the parent block.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: flex-end;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __end">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>justify-content: space-around</h2>
              <p>This property allows us to align our blocks at an equal distance from each other.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>
.d-flex{
  justify-content: space-around;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __sa">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>justify-content: space-evenly</h2>
              <p>The space-even property allows us to place our blocks at the same distance from each other. And on the sides of the screen, the distance increases.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: space-evenly;
}</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __se">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>
              
              <h2>justify-content: space-between</h2>
              <p>The space-between property allows us to erase borders and positions blocks across the entire width of the parent block with the distance between other blocks.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: space-between;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __sb">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>align-items: center + justify-content: center</h2>
              <p>The two display flex properties align-items and justify-content in tandem and do a very good job in various tasks. If you write center to each property, then the blocks will be in the center of the parent block.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __centr __ai">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>align-items: center + justify-content: space-around</h2>
              <p>Knowing what the justify-content: space-around property does, we will add align-items: center. And as a result, we can get an interesting arrangement of our blocks.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-around;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __sa __ai">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>align-items: flex-start (Default value) + justify-content: center</h2>
              <p>Default value align-items be flex-start. </p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: center;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __centr __ais">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

              <h2>align-items: flex-end + justify-content: center</h2>
              <p>These values will give you that our blocks will be at the bottom of the block.</p>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
<pre><code>.d-flex{
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: flex-end;
}
</code></pre>
<!-- ****************************************** -->
              <div class="d-flex __centr __aie">
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
                  <div class="item"></div>
              </div>

             

